36:23.987 --> 36:27.374
<i>He swore an oath to follow his dreams...</i>

36:27.454 --> 36:30.074
<i>...no matter how ridiculous...</i>

36:30.154 --> 36:34.555
<i>...to explore the shadows,
no matter how scary.</i>

36:36.920 --> 36:39.188
<i>And his vow was heard.</i>

36:40.521 --> 36:43.588
You absolute muppet!

36:44.787 --> 36:49.677
<i>When you're a kid, you want to explore
and see what's hiding in the shadows...</i>

36:49.756 --> 36:52.207
<i>...even if it scares the shit out of you.</i>

36:52.287 --> 36:54.721
<i>You'll cross the bridge over Cocytus.</i>

36:55.287 --> 36:56.979
<i>But...</i>

36:57.059 --> 37:00.476
<i>...as people grow older,
they lose that wonder.</i>

37:00.787 --> 37:04.455
<i>Scary things aren't fun anymore, just scary.</i>

37:05.320 --> 37:07.188
<i>So they shut them out.</i>

37:13.354 --> 37:17.041
<i>The dreams he once promised
to live were stored away in boxes...</i>

37:17.421 --> 37:19.674
<i>...stored away for another day...</i>

37:19.753 --> 37:23.840
<i>...and the days passed,
and the dreams were quickly forgotten.</i>

37:24.420 --> 37:25.878
<i>But...</i>

37:25.958 --> 37:28.633
<i>...abandon your dreams and they can become...</i>

37:29.654 --> 37:31.304
...resentful.

37:31.554 --> 37:35.954
<i>And as poor Edward let life's
little compromises accumulate...</i>

37:36.654 --> 37:41.223
<i>...the gap between who he was
and who he wanted to be...</i>

37:41.303 --> 37:43.186
<i>...grew larger.</i>

37:44.187 --> 37:48.421
<i>And as his dreams turned to darklings...</i>

37:48.521 --> 37:51.988
<i>...the sparkle faded from his eyes.</i>

38:01.854 --> 38:03.920
<i>Now he sits there...</i>

38:04.421 --> 38:07.174
<i>...in front of the TV, late into the night...</i>

38:07.254 --> 38:09.860
<i>...with the volume turned way up.</i>

38:10.254 --> 38:14.121
<i>And he knows that one day,
he'll have to pay the price...</i>

38:14.720 --> 38:18.787
<i>...for breaking his promise
and abandoning his dreams.</i>

38:26.953 --> 38:28.807
<i>And that price...</i>

38:28.887 --> 38:31.740
<i>...is why I don't ever...</i>

38:31.820 --> 38:33.887
<i>...want to grow up.</i>

38:42.320 --> 38:44.387
Shit! Get off!

38:48.454 --> 38:50.341
Do you expect me to believe that?

38:50.421 --> 38:54.898
Sometimes you have to pull back a piece
of reality when it gets in the way.

38:55.620 --> 38:57.355
I think you're full of shit.

38:58.521 --> 39:00.554
Take a look in the window.

39:04.953 --> 39:06.673
You look in it.

39:06.753 --> 39:08.907
I'm not the one that doesn't believe.

39:08.987 --> 39:10.773
It's, what...

39:10.853 --> 39:12.640
...twenty meters?

39:12.720 --> 39:14.374
Then I'll let you out.

40:13.820 --> 40:15.654
Trick or treat!

40:17.620 --> 40:19.198
Shit!

40:26.987 --> 40:28.988
Why the fuck did you do that?

40:29.720 --> 40:32.194
- Come on. It was funny.
- You know I hate being scared.

40:32.274 --> 40:34.074
No, I don't.

40:35.320 --> 40:37.640
The Corey I knew loved being scared.

40:37.720 --> 40:39.740
Halloween was his favorite day of the year.

40:39.820 --> 40:42.540
His head was full of dreams
he was gonna live.

40:42.620 --> 40:44.620
What happened to you?

40:48.120 --> 40:49.920
It's called survival.

40:51.187 --> 40:53.187
Law of the jungle.

40:53.687 --> 40:55.188
Survival.

41:02.288 --> 41:04.088
You clearly don't have a concussion.

41:06.454 --> 41:08.677
Find your own way home, right?

41:14.454 --> 41:15.734
Okay, truce.

41:17.287 --> 41:19.473
I'll stop trying to freak you out if...

41:19.553 --> 41:22.187
<i>...you stop running away for once.</i>

41:27.424 --> 41:29.520
I'll even make it up to you.

41:36.920 --> 41:38.421
How?

41:40.120 --> 41:41.640
School?

41:42.120 --> 41:43.604
Best years of our lives.

41:46.420 --> 41:49.220
You have a funny way
of making it up to people.

41:57.620 --> 41:59.487
Chuck us your board.

41:59.987 --> 42:01.787
What about security?

42:05.387 --> 42:07.587
Is there anything you're not scared of?

42:11.420 --> 42:13.487
I didn't say I was scared.

42:15.620 --> 42:17.720
I just have a cautionary nature.

43:50.787 --> 43:52.313
Boom.

44:08.319 --> 44:10.954
See? Easy as.

44:22.487 --> 44:25.034
You know, most people
aren't really scared of heights.

44:25.114 --> 44:27.553
At least... not of falling.

44:27.853 --> 44:29.854
What are they scared of, then?

44:30.620 --> 44:32.653
They're scared they'll jump.

44:35.887 --> 44:38.108
Is this the thing you wanted to show me?

44:38.587 --> 44:40.854
This is a thing I wanted to show you.

44:44.987 --> 44:48.241
Shit. What's with all the birds?

44:48.720 --> 44:51.520
They say animals know when they're gonna die.

44:52.220 --> 44:54.420
So they come here for their final moments.

44:56.120 --> 44:58.154
I like to keep them company.

45:00.087 --> 45:02.120
Nobody should die alone.

45:46.853 --> 45:48.943
When my dog died, he knew.

45:50.087 --> 45:53.353
Went off behind the rubbish tip
at the back of the yard.

45:54.887 --> 45:57.154
Took us, like, three days to find him.

46:00.053 --> 46:01.920
My mum knew.

46:02.753 --> 46:06.767
She was always worried, 'cause she had me
late, that she wouldn't always be around.

46:10.286 --> 46:14.887
That's why she always used to tell stories
about fantasy lands where I'd be safe.

46:17.687 --> 46:19.920
It's one way to survive, I guess.

46:27.853 --> 46:30.253
Is that why she always played that song?

46:31.120 --> 46:32.695
You remember that?

46:37.348 --> 46:42.971
<i>When you walk through a storm</i>

46:43.051 --> 46:48.273
<i>Hold your head up high</i>

46:48.353 --> 46:50.020
You shouldn't sing.

46:54.520 --> 46:56.540
It's bullshit, anyway.

46:56.820 --> 46:58.673
"You'll never walk alone."

46:58.753 --> 47:00.707
I'd rather be alone.

47:00.787 --> 47:03.054
No one to rely on but yourself.

47:03.386 --> 47:05.653
No one to drag you down.

47:06.219 --> 47:08.718
Nobody to have your back either.

47:10.653 --> 47:13.339
I remember this exhibition at the museum.

47:13.419 --> 47:15.253
There was a quote.

47:15.553 --> 47:19.354
"Man is by nature a social animal.

47:19.987 --> 47:23.988
Anyone who does not partake of society...

47:25.020 --> 47:26.854
...is either a beast...

47:28.620 --> 47:30.420
...or a God."

47:32.353 --> 47:35.109
Jango would say you're a little lamb.

47:35.189 --> 47:37.253
At least I'm not a beast.

47:37.807 --> 47:40.471
Can you say the same, dances with wolves?

47:50.386 --> 47:54.220
If there's one thing I won't miss,
it's these corridors.

47:59.219 --> 48:01.487
Feels like we should do a nudie run.

48:06.019 --> 48:08.220
Or you too scared of security?

48:10.453 --> 48:13.339
It's not security you need
to be worried about.

48:13.420 --> 48:15.907
It's the wolves in the walls that'll get ya.

48:16.619 --> 48:19.086
<i>I hoped we were done with these stories.</i>

48:19.853 --> 48:21.654
<i>This isn't a story.</i>

48:22.286 --> 48:24.553
<i>Everyone notices different things.</i>

48:25.253 --> 48:27.654
Some notice the moment you change your hair.

48:28.453 --> 48:31.253
Others always notice
what shoes you're wearing.

48:33.453 --> 48:35.087
I noticed them change.

48:39.453 --> 48:42.120
<i>It was the smell I noticed first.</i>

48:43.019 --> 48:47.053
<i>The stench of twisting, multiplying hormones.</i>

48:47.988 --> 48:50.110
<i>It always preceded them.</i>

48:50.520 --> 48:54.320
<i>No amount of cheap safeway
deodorant can cover that odor.</i>

48:59.887 --> 49:03.120
I saw skin disappear
beneath unwelcome hair...

49:03.940 --> 49:06.840
<i>...voices deepen into growls.</i>

49:06.920 --> 49:09.120
<i>Like a virus, it spread.</i>

49:09.753 --> 49:12.373
<i>And once that toxin poisons you...</i>

49:12.853 --> 49:16.127
<i>...you're capable of doing things
you never thought you'd do...</i>

49:16.787 --> 49:18.888
<i>...all in the name of survival.</i>

49:24.514 --> 49:27.009
<i>No matter where you hide...</i>

49:27.089 --> 49:28.969
<i>...they sniff you out.</i>

49:40.653 --> 49:42.720
And for those that didn't change...

49:44.387 --> 49:46.654
<i>...those that were left behind...</i>

49:53.019 --> 49:55.887
<i>...those that didn't have
the taste for blood...</i>

49:59.986 --> 50:03.000
<i>...there was only one thing you could do.</i>

50:34.653 --> 50:35.841
Jonah!

50:59.787 --> 51:01.320
Jonah?

51:19.720 --> 51:21.787
There's only one thing you can do.

52:37.786 --> 52:41.440
Welcome to the library, the sanctuary
for geeks, freaks and outcasts.

52:41.520 --> 52:44.608
Guess you're one of us now.
One of us! One of us!

52:44.688 --> 52:47.573
- Why'd you disappear?
- To see how you liked it.

52:47.653 --> 52:50.487
- I didn't.
- Well, color me surprised.

53:04.520 --> 53:08.140
- Is there another way out of here?
- In a coffin?

53:08.220 --> 53:10.367
You really are no help.

53:23.587 --> 53:26.038
Well, I guess we're saved, then.

53:26.118 --> 53:27.906
- Wait.
- What?

53:27.986 --> 53:30.813
They're your friends.
What's the worst they could do?

53:30.893 --> 53:33.117
How's this for a chaos theory, arsehole?

53:35.252 --> 53:37.188
Yeah, Jango.

53:37.388 --> 53:40.187
He decked you sober.
You don't want to see him pissed.

53:41.253 --> 53:42.806
There you go.

53:42.886 --> 53:45.086
- Cheers.
- Wear that.

53:52.186 --> 53:55.187
He won't hurt me if he knows
I'm with you. Right?

53:59.752 --> 54:02.220
You still don't want to be seen with me.

54:04.119 --> 54:06.520
Nobody means anything to you, do they?

54:12.653 --> 54:14.920
Shitty books that you love so much.

54:19.553 --> 54:21.554
Shove these fireworks...

54:24.253 --> 54:25.689
I've got an idea.

54:27.952 --> 54:29.819
Shut up.

54:30.519 --> 54:32.406
Did you hear something?

54:32.486 --> 54:34.406
Wait, what?

54:34.486 --> 54:36.487
Come out and play.

54:39.219 --> 54:41.487
Where are you?

55:10.819 --> 55:12.620
Thank you.

55:37.520 --> 55:41.521
Do you know Laura Premble?
This place kinda reminds me of her.

55:43.019 --> 55:46.287
This isn't one of those
"Penthouse forum" stories, is it?

55:47.319 --> 55:50.772
Well... she was the first person
I, you know...

55:50.852 --> 55:53.053
...fooled around with.

55:54.453 --> 55:57.686
But no, a bunch of us
came here after year 11 formal.

55:58.719 --> 56:02.153
I barely knew her, but...
everyone was pairing up.

56:02.953 --> 56:04.819
I remember thinking...

56:05.253 --> 56:07.053
"...jackpot!"

56:10.019 --> 56:11.886
You liked her?

56:12.186 --> 56:13.753
Yeah.

56:15.652 --> 56:18.139
But, man, she could drink.

56:18.219 --> 56:20.487
She drank so much.

56:29.053 --> 56:31.120
She just got kinda quiet.

56:36.119 --> 56:38.753
She just sat there staring off into the dark.

56:44.886 --> 56:49.172
And she dropped a bottle. It smashed
on the concrete. She didn't even move.

56:56.353 --> 56:58.586
It's like she wasn't really there.

57:04.286 --> 57:06.353
It's not much of a story, I guess.

57:07.186 --> 57:09.020
What'd you do after formal?

57:11.319 --> 57:12.853
I didn't go.

57:16.153 --> 57:17.953
Oh, well...

57:22.153 --> 57:23.949
...I guess you didn't miss much.

58:04.219 --> 58:07.806
<i>Miss Susie had a steamboat,
the steamboat had a bell</i>

58:07.886 --> 58:11.713
<i>Miss Susie went to heaven,
the steamboat went to...</i>

58:15.519 --> 58:19.073
<i>Hello, operator, give me number nine</i>

58:19.153 --> 58:21.774
<i>- If you disconnect me
- I'll chop off your...</i>

58:21.854 --> 58:25.472
<i>Behind the refrigerator,
there was a piece of glass</i>

58:25.552 --> 58:28.516
<i>Miss Susie sat upon it,
and broke her little...</i>

58:28.596 --> 58:31.737
<i>Ask me no more questions,
tell me no more lies</i>

58:31.817 --> 58:33.627
<i>The boys are in the bathroom</i>

58:33.707 --> 58:36.340
<i>Zipping up their... flies are in the meadow</i>

58:36.420 --> 58:37.974
<i>Bees are in the park</i>

58:38.054 --> 58:41.974
<i>Miss Susie and her boyfriend
are kissing in the D-A-R-K</i>

58:42.054 --> 58:45.711
<i>D-A-R-K, D-A-R-K...</i>

58:58.253 --> 59:00.119
You still hungry?

59:23.586 --> 59:25.539
What the fuck? It's just me.

59:25.619 --> 59:27.486
I thought you hated Halloween.

59:29.619 --> 59:31.652
Twick or tweat.

59:34.886 --> 59:37.686
Here. You stink.

59:39.786 --> 59:41.839
It's not my fault there's a heatwave.

59:41.919 --> 59:45.719
It's the hole in the ozone layer.
Those spray cans don't help.

59:48.219 --> 59:50.953
You know in some places
it snows on Halloween?

59:51.986 --> 59:54.036
You like snow?

59:54.219 --> 59:56.053
I've never seen it.

59:57.419 --> 01:00:00.652
That's why I'm saving up all
my slave wage from this dump.

01:00:01.452 --> 01:00:03.719
So I can fly away to Canada.

01:00:04.419 --> 01:00:06.253
Get a log cabin.

01:00:07.719 --> 01:00:09.606
It snows most of the year there.

01:00:09.686 --> 01:00:12.753
The rivers are so frozen,
you can skate on them.

01:00:16.352 --> 01:00:18.786
It snows quite a bit in New York too.

01:00:21.086 --> 01:00:23.153
You're gonna go, aren't you?

01:00:29.253 --> 01:00:31.273
Did you ever let down a friend?

01:00:31.352 --> 01:00:33.366
Like stand someone up?

01:00:33.816 --> 01:00:37.159
Sure. If I had a dollar
for every person I left waiting...

01:00:37.239 --> 01:00:39.519
...under the clocks at Flinders Street...

01:00:42.153 --> 01:00:44.019
...I'd have nine dollars.

01:00:44.786 --> 01:00:46.287
No.

01:00:48.119 --> 01:00:49.986
I mean...

01:00:51.586 --> 01:00:55.586
...did you ever say that you'd be there
for someone no matter what...

01:00:58.002 --> 01:01:00.002
...and then you weren't?

01:01:02.385 --> 01:01:04.820
I had this one friend in primary school.

01:01:06.986 --> 01:01:10.606
She even joined me at callispastics,
even though she was a total unco.

01:01:10.786 --> 01:01:12.652
What happened to her?

01:01:15.385 --> 01:01:17.419
Never really thought about it.

01:01:19.186 --> 01:01:21.281
I went to a different high school...

01:01:21.770 --> 01:01:23.983
...started hanging out with other girls.

01:01:24.652 --> 01:01:26.686
The cool kids, you know.

01:01:28.786 --> 01:01:32.253
I just couldn't keep playing
with my little ponies forever, right?

01:01:35.219 --> 01:01:38.687
I guess I didn't notice when the gaps
between us got bigger and bigger.

01:01:41.752 --> 01:01:43.753
I haven't seen her for years.

01:01:46.352 --> 01:01:48.386
She was just a friend.

01:01:49.852 --> 01:01:51.386
Why?

01:01:53.953 --> 01:01:56.986
I guess sometimes you don't realize
who you've left behind.

01:02:00.519 --> 01:02:02.553
Or who's right in front of you.

01:02:06.919 --> 01:02:08.419
Yeah.

01:02:09.518 --> 01:02:10.903
Maybe.

01:02:13.739 --> 01:02:17.386
Or maybe you could get out
of your fucking diapers for once.

01:02:17.919 --> 01:02:22.006
You think you're frustrated here?
Try living in the same world in a skirt...

01:02:22.086 --> 01:02:25.639
...surrounded by a bunch of babies
who don't even notice you.

01:02:25.719 --> 01:02:28.131
Why can't you guys just grow up?

01:02:28.210 --> 01:02:30.226
Girls do! We just stand here...

01:02:30.306 --> 01:02:35.016
...waiting, while you guys are stuck
with your heads in the... trees.

01:02:37.086 --> 01:02:39.806
Is this 'cause I didn't
thank you for the slurpee?

01:02:39.886 --> 01:02:41.690
I don't under...

01:03:12.752 --> 01:03:14.619
We do want to grow up.

01:03:15.819 --> 01:03:18.672
There's just a part of us
that doesn't want to stop.

01:03:18.752 --> 01:03:20.319
Stop?

01:03:23.686 --> 01:03:25.552
Climbing trees.

01:03:28.060 --> 01:03:30.119
Trick or treat!

01:03:31.452 --> 01:03:32.953
Great.

01:03:40.218 --> 01:03:43.706
Well! Ring-a-ding-ding, cozza.

01:03:43.786 --> 01:03:47.106
You sly hound. Thought your head was hurting.

01:03:47.185 --> 01:03:48.973
Turns out you were just hurting for head.

01:03:49.053 --> 01:03:51.339
- Real smooth.
- Thank you.

01:03:51.419 --> 01:03:54.286
So? Where have you been?

01:03:55.218 --> 01:03:58.622
- Looking everywhere for you.
- Don't tell me you were getting bored?

01:03:58.702 --> 01:04:01.386
Hey, Bobby. Want to go for a ride?

01:04:03.686 --> 01:04:05.186
Hey.

01:04:06.118 --> 01:04:07.683
You're not...

01:04:07.763 --> 01:04:10.792
...pissed about before, are ya?

01:04:12.085 --> 01:04:15.152
I mean, any hole's a goal, you know.

01:04:15.886 --> 01:04:18.285
Maybe you shouldn't talk about her like that.

01:04:20.419 --> 01:04:23.407
Is this true love? It is, isn't it?

01:04:50.953 --> 01:04:54.761
Anyway, we're not done yet.
The night's not over. Copies ready?

01:04:54.941 --> 01:04:56.519
Almost.

01:04:59.552 --> 01:05:01.419
Forget something?

01:05:05.852 --> 01:05:07.773
Hey, guess what we found at the cemetery.

01:05:07.853 --> 01:05:10.569
- What?
- The little fag's mother.

01:05:10.649 --> 01:05:12.143
Yeah.

01:05:12.223 --> 01:05:15.046
And wait till you see
what we did to her tombstone.

01:05:15.485 --> 01:05:17.552
We're gonna need photos of it.

01:05:17.652 --> 01:05:21.089
So... grab your shit. Let's go.

01:05:21.818 --> 01:05:23.538
Got everything?

01:05:23.618 --> 01:05:27.272
- Slushy. Did you get me my slushy?
- Yeah, yeah. I got your slushy.

01:05:27.452 --> 01:05:29.105
Thank you.

01:05:29.185 --> 01:05:30.719
Nah.

01:05:33.952 --> 01:05:35.452
What?

01:05:39.619 --> 01:05:41.419
What's the problem, cozza?

01:05:42.018 --> 01:05:44.419
Is he your boyfriend or something?

01:05:48.686 --> 01:05:51.285
- I don't want to be like that.
- Like what?

01:05:52.552 --> 01:05:54.052
Cruel.

01:05:56.953 --> 01:05:59.205
Didn't know you batted for that team.

01:05:59.285 --> 01:06:01.185
What if I did?

01:06:01.265 --> 01:06:03.352
Would you still be my friend?

01:06:03.686 --> 01:06:06.233
Or would you throw dead animals at my house?

01:06:06.313 --> 01:06:09.305
Alright, what... what are you saying, man?

01:06:09.385 --> 01:06:11.372
Maybe I'm not one of you anymore.

01:06:12.451 --> 01:06:13.985
Hey.

01:06:14.852 --> 01:06:16.686
You are one of us.

01:06:17.719 --> 01:06:19.552
Or you're nobody.

01:06:19.953 --> 01:06:22.187
I guess you're friends with nobody, then?

01:06:22.816 --> 01:06:24.663
Fuck you!

01:06:25.720 --> 01:06:29.266
Fight! Fight!
Fight, fight, fight, fight, fight, fight!

01:06:46.485 --> 01:06:48.018
Mate.

01:06:48.786 --> 01:06:50.332
Nah.

01:07:03.752 --> 01:07:04.986
Corey!

01:07:19.019 --> 01:07:20.586
Fuck.

01:07:43.152 --> 01:07:44.719
Jonah!

01:07:46.586 --> 01:07:48.652
Jonah? You in there?

01:07:49.985 --> 01:07:51.486
Jonah?

01:08:15.418 --> 01:08:19.506
<i>Now he sits there, in front of the TV...</i>

01:08:19.586 --> 01:08:23.185
<i>...late into the night,
with the volume turned way up.</i>

01:12:08.751 --> 01:12:10.552
Turn off the light.

01:12:24.685 --> 01:12:26.552
Why'd you leave?

